Description:
The path gets narrower with each step until you find yourselves looking down into the depths of the temple.

There are stairs carved into the temple’s vertical wall, very dangerous and poorly maintained. In their current condition, these stairs are a challenge even for expert climbers! It is clear that this is not the main entrance to the depths of the temple.

Using them in their current state may be difficult, but it is the only way to continue, and a group full of veteran adventurers like you is not afraid of the potential risk of slipping and falling to your death!
